<s docid="FT942-2917" num="4"> FT 17 JUN 94 / Women priests vote</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT942-2917" num="5"> The General Synod of the Scottish Episcopal Church - part of the Anglican communion - yesterday gave the go-ahead for the ordination of women.</s>

<s docid="FT942-2917" num="6"> The proposal required the received two-thirds majority in the three voting groups at the synod - the bishops, the laity and the clergy.</s>
