<HEADLINE>

<s docid="FT934-11863" num="4"> FT 29 OCT 93 / High Court rules on women priests</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT934-11863" num="5"> THE Church of England's General Synod did not exceed its powers when it asked parliament to approve a legislative measure for the ordination of women, the High Court said yesterday.</s>

<s docid="FT934-11863" num="6"> It ruled against the Church Society, which had argued that an act of parliament was needed to sanction the move as it amounted to a 'funda mental change' in Church doctrine.</s>

<s docid="FT934-11863" num="7"> The Church Society said it would not appeal.</s>
</TEXT>
