<HEADLINE>

<s docid="FT924-6652" num="4"> FT 20 NOV 92 / Former Bishop of London plans move to Roman Catholic church in protest at vote for women priests</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT924-6652" num="5"> GRAHAM LEONARD, former bishop of London, is planning to join the Roman Catholic Church in protest at last week's vote in favour of the ordination of women priests.</s>

<s docid="FT924-6652" num="6"> The bishop, third most senior in the Anglican hierarchy until he retired last year, suggested in an article in the Catholic Herald that a breakaway church might be formed under the authority of the Pope.</s>

<s docid="FT924-6652" num="7"> The archbishop of Canterbury, Dr George Carey, yesterday called for 'ill-considered judgments' to be avoided.</s>
</TEXT>
